  <h1>No Biting / Chewing</h1>

  <h3>🦴 Reducing Hand Biting</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Redirect Immediately:</strong> Say “Ouch!” calmly, stop movement, and offer a toy.</li>
    <li><strong>Stop Play If Needed:</strong> If redirection fails, walk away briefly. Return and retry.</li>
    <li><strong>Teach Gentle Mouth:</strong> Let pup explore hands calmly—reward licking or sniffing, withdraw attention for biting.</li>
  </ol>

  <h3>🏠 Preventing Inappropriate Chewing</h3>
  <ol>
    <li><strong>Puppy-Proof:</strong> Remove tempting items. Use baby gates/playpens to limit freedom.</li>
    <li><strong>Chew Alternatives:</strong> Offer 3–5 toys like KONGs, Nylabones, frozen teething rings.</li>
    <li><strong>Interrupt & Redirect:</strong> Use “Leave it,” guide to toy, and reward chewing it.</li>
    <li><strong>Taste Deterrents:</strong> Use Bitter Apple on furniture—test first!</li>
  </ol>

  <h4>✅ Do This</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Supervise often, rotate toys, teach “Leave it” early</li>
    <li>Use frozen options for teething relief</li>
  </ul>

  <h4>❌ Avoid This</h4>
  <ul>
    <li>Don’t punish, shout, or use hands to correct</li>
    <li>Don’t give old socks/shoes—they confuse the message</li>
  </ul>

